She was very lonely and sad, looking for her purpose in life, until she discovered about "Love", how wonderful love is, HER WINGS REPRESENTED HER LOVE AND CARE, so she sets out to give love and help people find love, the ones she helped some found love and it worked well, others not so much, even so, at least they have/had loved which was better than not having loved at all, she became desperate and kept giving herself to just about anyone, but these people always end up loving someone else (hence the scene where she was stabbing people). Not having a love and not having someone love her back, made her feel life is not worth living, so she GIVES UP and STOPS LOVING, her death in the scene I think is more of a symbolism, when a person stops their own heart from loving or caring at all, or just gives up hope about finding love. In the scene when she was totally unconscious a man came into her life and finally made her heart BEAT again, and this time she sees him, and is a symbol for her loving him, him being the object of her affection. He caused her to live again. - That is my interpretation.

I am a Christian teacher and I think many of you are not taking the time to examine what scripture says about something. I did this as well, before attending school. The Bible was written by many authors and over different time periods. So, if you don't understand the author or his audience you may take versus to mean something they don't. First of all the old testament is just that the old law. It does say in the Bible that being homosexual is a death sentence for your soul. However, that is not what should be focused on at all. God does not endorse hate and judgement on others, Instead he made his greatest law the one to love one another..unconditionally.
